   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LIFE-STUDY OF JEREMIAH MESSAGE THIRTY-FIVE JEHOVAH'S PUNISHMENT</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>AND JUDGMENT UPON THE NATIONS</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>INVOLVED WITH GOD'S ELECT, ISRAEL 2 Scripture Reading: Jer 48 49</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>In this message we will continue to consider God's judgment upon the nations involved with God's elect, Israel.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>III.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>JEHOVAH'S PUNISHMENT</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>AND JUDGMENT UPON MOAB</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>In chapter forty-eight we see Jehovah's punishment and judgment upon Moab.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>A. A Nation Typifying the World of Fleshly Lust</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>That Corrupts and Frustrates God's Chosen People</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>through the Greedy Religionists</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Moab as a nation typifies the world of fleshly lust that corrupts and frustrates God's chosen people through the greedy religionists from following and walking with God in His holy way Num 25:1-5; Deut 23:3-4; Rev 2:14 .</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>It was Moab who hired Balaam, the Gentile prophet, to stumble the children of Israel.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>B. Moab, the First Forefather of the Moabites</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Moab, as the first forefather of the Moabites, was born of Lot through incest with his daughter Gen 19:30-38 .</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>In the sight of God, the source of Moab was most evil.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>C. The Moabites Not Being Allowed</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>to Enter into the Assembly of Jehovah</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The Moabites were not allowed to enter into the assembly of Jehovah even to the tenth generation Deut 23:3 .</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>However, a Moabitess by the name of Ruth became the mother of one of the prominent forefathers of Christ Matt 1:5b because of her allegiance to Israel in the interest of God Ruth 1:14-18 .</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>This indicates that although the Moabites were condemned, at a certain time God had compassion on them.</S>
   </TEXT>
